<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="snprintf" id="snprintf">snprintf</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="cpp code cpp"><span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdio&gt;</span>
&nbsp;
<span class="kw4">int</span> <span class="kw3">snprintf</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy2">*</span>buffer, <span class="kw4">int</span> buff_size, <span class="kw4">const</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy2">*</span>format, ... <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre><div class="table sectionedit2"><table class="inline">
	<tr class="row0">
		<td class="col0"><a href="../../c_0x" class="wikilink1" title="c_0x">C++0x</a> feature</td>
	</tr>
</table></div>
<!-- EDIT2 TABLE [124-144] -->
<p>

Loads data from the given locations and writes them to the given character string accorcing to the <code>format</code> parameter. At most <code>buff_size</code> characters are written.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "snprintf" [1-313] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit3"><a name="parameters" id="parameters">Parameters</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

<code>buffer</code> - pointer to a character string to print to
</p>

<p>
<code>buff_size</code> - maximum number of characters to write
</p>

<p>
<code>format</code> - pointer to a character string specifying how to print the given arguments. See <a href="printf_format" class="wikilink1" title="io:c:printf_format">this</a> for more information.
</p>

<p>
<code>. . .</code> - pointers to the additional arguments. See <a href="printf_format" class="wikilink1" title="io:c:printf_format">this</a> for more information.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT3 SECTION "Parameters" [314-682] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit4"><a name="return_value" id="return_value">Return value</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

number of characters written if successful or negative value if an error occurred. If the resulting string gets truncated due to <code>buff_size</code> limit, function returns the total number of characters (not including the terminating null-byte) which would have been written, if the limit was not imposed.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT4 SECTION "Return value" [683-1006] -->
